      <!-- WikiBreeze coll1 start--><h2>Hi-ZJU</h2><p>Together with Hi-ZJU, we went to Fuzhou, Fujian Province, China for <strong>a volunteer teaching activity</strong>. Through education, we help students <strong>in poor areas and rural areas</strong> to obtain <strong>better educational resources and improve their learning ability and knowledge level</strong>.</p><image-pro><image-pro src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4591/wiki/wikibreezeupload/collaboration/coll1/6e68a6c5cbc882e7726a20c38887e7f933a5453f.jpg"></image-pro><p><strong>Fig. 1. </strong>Synthetic biology lesson in Fujian</p></image-pro><image-pro><image-pro src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4591/wiki/wikibreezeupload/collaboration/coll1/f78f12c26d2bae9b9b059e50f5dda56493ae977e.jpg"></image-pro><p><strong>Fig. 2. </strong>Mapping animal cell structure</p></image-pro><image-pro><image-pro src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4591/wiki/wikibreezeupload/collaboration/coll1/fa7bc95942bedc0b1e87e59850e17861295ef287.jpg"></image-pro><p><strong>Fig. 3. </strong>Children in painting</p></image-pro><h3>LZU-CHINA</h3><p>We also went to Zhangye City, Gansu Province, China for voluntary education activities with the LZU-CHINA team. We strive to change the education situation <strong>in poor areas and rural areas</strong> through the power of education，and provide students with <strong>better education conditions and opportunities</strong> ，so that they can have<strong> a better future</strong>.</p><image-pro><image-pro src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4591/wiki/wikibreezeupload/collaboration/coll1/24ff39ef9926b2897b236e0cec3721412fad629d.jpg"></image-pro><p><strong>Fig. 4. </strong>Answered the questions actively</p></image-pro><image-pro><image-pro src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4591/wiki/wikibreezeupload/collaboration/coll1/516e0b65ab21be7009ec12a22cb07a6653df8b8a.jpg"></image-pro><p><strong>Fig. 5. </strong>Synthetic biology lesson in Gansu</p></image-pro><h3>NNU-CHINA</h3><p>We have had many exchanges with NNU-CHINA. On July 18, we attended <strong>the Environmental Protection and Sustainable Development Summit </strong>hosted by NNU-CHINA. On August 5, NNU-CHINA participated in the academic forum on <strong>Bioremediation</strong> organized by us. On August 19, we met at <strong>the 14th China Enzyme Engineering Symposium</strong> and exchanged views on the progress of the project. Through constant communication, we can clearly discover the <strong>subtleties</strong> of their team project design and teamwork, and then compare ourselves and make <strong>continuous progress</strong>.</p><p>In addition, we jointly designed a <strong>questionnaire </strong>with NNU-CHINA. Through cooperation, we can obtain samples from <strong>different regions and different groups</strong>, broaden <strong>the breadth and depth </strong>of the <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="http://research.It">research.It</a> is also a good way to improve<strong> the</strong> <strong>representativeness and credibility </strong>of the research, and improve <strong>the progress and efficiency</strong> of the research.</p><image-pro><image-pro src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4591/wiki/wikibreezeupload/collaboration/coll1/39e674c3fe29c0dd5ca91bf0b914ebe33d1acc95.jpg"></image-pro><p><strong>Fig. 6. </strong>Photo with NNU-China</p></image-pro><image-pro><image-pro src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4591/wiki/wikibreezeupload/collaboration/coll1/c70c006d9f02de1c9dd5d70634b43b2b6c35268e.jpg"></image-pro><p><strong>Fig. 7. </strong>Post-meeting exchange</p></image-pro><image-pro><image-pro src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4591/wiki/wikibreezeupload/collaboration/coll1/85861d6d1070890fafe6f9772fac7e08e11a1869.jpg"></image-pro><p><strong>Fig. 8. </strong>Environmental and Sustainable Development Summit poster</p></image-pro><h3>Bioplus-China</h3><p>At the invitation of Bioplus-China, we participated in the <strong>Synthetic Biology Exchange meeting</strong> on August 5. Other teams participating in this meeting were Bioplus-Shanghai, ZJU-China, and OTIA-Hangzhou. At the meeting, we actively<strong> talk about ideas and provide advice and help</strong> for each other&apos;s projects.</p><p>At the invitation of Bioplus-China, we have <strong>set up a science education booth</strong> with Bioplus-Shanghai, ZJU-China, and OTIA-Hangzhou in Hangzhou Low Carbon Science and Technology Museum, China, to promote synthetic biology, iGEM competition, and our project to visitors. Together, we <strong>call on more people to join in the shaping of synthetic biology.This is a good way to</strong> <strong>increase the influence of iGEM competition in China</strong>, and <strong>promote the spread of synthetic biology in China</strong>.</p><!-- WikiBreeze coll1 end-->
