  <h3>SZU-China</h3>
  <p>SZU-China contacted us through the iGEM China Team Liaison Group,and had a friendly exchange on the experimental design as both of our teams intend to use Bacillus subtilis in our chassis biology this year. In the process of communication, we found that SZU-China needed pMA5 plasmid, and our team happened to have a lot of it, so we sent the plasmid to SZU-China. SZU-China also provided some suggestions and help for the experimental design of our degradation module.
On August 5, SZU-China participated in the special academic forum on Bioremediation organized by us, contributing to the success of the forum.</p>
